Sentencas: Micromachined fuel cells are among a class of microscale devices being explored for portable power generation.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: In this paper, we report processing and geometric design criteria for the fabrication of free-standing electrolyte membranes for microscale solid-oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Submicron, dense, nanocrystalline yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) and gadolinium-doped ceria (GDC) films were deposited onto silicon nitride membranes using electron-beam evaporation and sputter deposition.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Selective silicon nitride removal leads to free-standing, square, electrolyte membranes with side dimensions as large as 1025 mum for YSZ and 525 mum for GDC, with high processing yields for YSZ.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Residual stresses are tensile (+85 to +235 MPa) and compressive (-865 to -155 MPa) in as-deposited evaporated and sputtered films, respectively.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Tensile evaporated films fail via brittle fracture during annealing at temperatures below 773 K; thermal limitations are dependent on the film thickness to membrane size aspect ratio.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Sputtered films with compressive residual stresses show superior mechanical and thermal stability than evaporated films.
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Sputtered 1025-mum membranes survive annealing at 773 K, which leads to the generation of tensile stresses and brittle fracture at elevated temperatures (923 K).
Titulo: Fabrication and structural characterization of self-supporting electrolyte membranes for a micro solid-oxide fuel cell
